 
  
 <p class="titulo_2_noticia_azul_oscuro"><strong>Postdoctoral positions in Education in Chile </strong></p>
 <p>Four postdoctoral positions are being offered at  the Center for Advanced Research in Education (CIAE) at the Institute of  Education of the Universidad de Chile, located in the city of Santiago, the  capital of Chile. The positions are in any of the following research areas (<strong>for  more details about each area please go to the specific link</strong>).</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Language and Literacy Teaching and Learning  (</strong><a href="https://www.ciae.uchile.cl/index.php?page=view_noticias&id=2037" target="_blank"><strong>More details)</strong></a></li>
   <li><strong>Teacher Professional Development  (<a href="https://www.ciae.uchile.cl/index.php?page=view_noticias&id=2034" target="_blank">More details</a>)</strong></li>

  <li><strong>Integrated STEM  (</strong><a href="https://www.ciae.uchile.cl/index.php?page=view_noticias&id=2036" target="_blank"><strong>More details)</strong></a></li>

  <li><strong>Education Policy  (<a href="https://www.ciae.uchile.cl/index.php?page=view_noticias&id=2035" target="_blank">More details</a>)</strong></li>
 </ul>
 <p>Candidates should exhibit evidence of outstanding  research results and should have received a PhD between January 2018 and November 16, 2020.</p>
<p>The position is for full-time research activity,  with no teaching duties. The preparation of the candidates and their interests  should enable them to contribute to the research agenda of CIAE.</p>
<p>CIAE will cover flight tickets, and will pay a  monthly salary of Ch$1,800,000 (before taxes, around US$2,400).</p>
<p>The application process will be opened until&nbsp;<strong>November 16, 2020.</strong></p>
<p>After completing the application form you will  receive a confirmation email with a link that you must send to the people who  will write your recommendation letters.</p>
<p>Applications for which two recommendations are not  received by the application deadline will not be considered.</p>
